From 6012022e8733afd264a44ec663bf5d7028b07c10 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Philipp Stanner <phasta@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 23 Apr 2025 09:53:41 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ALSA: echoaudio: Use pure devres PCI
Git-commit: 6012022e8733afd264a44ec663bf5d7028b07c10
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
References: jsc#PED-14430 jsc#PED-14297 jsc#PED-14024

pci_request_regions() is a hybrid function which becomes managed if
pcim_enable_device() was called before. This hybrid nature is deprecated
and should not be used anymore.

Replace pci_request_regions() with the always-managed function
pcim_request_all_regions().

Signed-off-by: Philipp Stanner <phasta@kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Andy Shevchenko <andriy.shevchenko@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250423075346.45907-24-phasta@kernel.org

---
 sound/pci/echoaudio/echoaudio.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/sound/pci/echoaudio/echoaudio.c b/sound/pci/echoaudio/echoaudio.c
index 4effcc0090ac..80d8ce75fdbb 100644
--- a/sound/pci/echoaudio/echoaudio.c
+++ b/sound/pci/echoaudio/echoaudio.c
@@ -1910,7 +1910,7 @@ static int snd_echo_create(struct snd_card *card,
 	chip->can_set_rate = 1;
 
 	/* PCI resource allocation */
-	err = pci_request_regions(pci, ECHOCARD_NAME);
+	err = pcim_request_all_regions(pci, ECHOCARD_NAME);
 	if (err < 0)
 		return err;
 
